<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14970] New releases must supply SHA-256 and/or SHA-512 checksums</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14970</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Release policy was updated around 9/2018 to state:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;For new releases, PMCs MUST supply SHA-256 and/or SHA-512; and SHOULD NOT supply MD5 or SHA-1. Existing releases do not need to be changed.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;build.xml needs to be updated from MD5 &amp;amp; SHA-1 to, at least, SHA-256 or both. cassandra-builds/cassandra-release&#160;scripts need to be updated to work with the new checksum files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apache.org/dev/release-distribution#sigs-and-sums&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.apache.org/dev/release-distribution#sigs-and-sums&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
